entries.title: Video shows Russian cruise missile flying toward Kyiv
entries.description: Explosions rattled villages and cities across Ukraine, damaging civilian infrastructure and killing at least three people in what Kyiv has called one of Russia's biggest missile barrages since the war began. CNN's Ben Wedeman reports from Kyiv.

entries.title: Meet some of the new species discovered in 2022
entries.description: The tree of life grew in 2022 as California Academy of Sciences researchers and their international collaborators discovered 146 new animal, plant and fungi species.

entries.title: Chinese fighter jet intercepts US recon aircraft with 'unsafe maneuver,' US says
entries.description: A Chinese fighter jet intercepted a US reconnaissance aircraft over the South China Sea last week and performed an "unsafe maneuver," forcing the US aircraft to take evasive action, according to Indo-Pacific Command, the command responsible for overseeing US military operations in the region.

entries.title: Vivienne Westwood, fashion designer and style icon, dies at 81
entries.description: British fashion designer and style icon Vivienne Westwood has died aged 81. She passed away peacefully at her home in London on Thursday, according to an official statement from her eponymous company.

entries.title: Santos' claim about his mother and 9/11 faces scrutiny amid his other lies
entries.description: As Rep.-elect George Santos continues to face scrutiny for false claims the New York Republican has made about his biography, another story is being questioned: that his mother was at the World Trade Center on September 11, 2001, and that the incident played a role in her death.

entries.title: Brazilian soccer legend Pelé dies at 82
entries.description: Pelé, the Brazilian soccer legend who won three World Cups and became the sport's first global icon, has died at the age of 82, according to a statement from his daughter Kely Nascimento on Instagram.

entries.title: Watch passenger's enthusiastic reunion with his missing luggage
entries.description: Patrick Keane, who traveled to Chicago after two canceled flights, had an enthusiastic reunion with his luggage that he says had been missing for a week.

entries.title: Three young children trapped in car crash wreckage for days
entries.description: A 5-year-old girl in Australia saved her baby brother's life after a car crash killed their parents, leaving three young children trapped in the wreckage in searing temperatures for more than two days. Reporter Ashtyn Hiron with CNN affiliate 9 News has the details.

entries.title: Highlights from the latest release of January 6 transcripts
entries.description: The House January 6 committee on Thursday released another wave of witness interview transcripts.

entries.title: Professor tears up diplomas on TV to protest Taliban ban on women's education
entries.description: A Kabul professor tore up his diplomas live on television in Afghanistan in protest over the Taliban's barring of women from higher education.

entries.title: See stunning footage of a partially frozen Niagara Falls
entries.description: Ice from a massive winter storm that hit the US and Canada has turned the iconic waterfalls into a winter wonderland.

entries.title: Massive hunt for missing 11-year-old faces challenges, police say
entries.description: The massive hunt for missing 11-year-old Madalina Cojocari has been hampered by how late police in North Carolina were notified of her disappearance, Cornelius police Capt. Jennifer Thompson said in a video update.

entries.title: Why Southwest is still melting down
entries.description: It's Thursday. The Christmas storm that dumped many feet of snow across most of America was mostly over by Monday. Still, Southwest canceled another 2,300 flights today, long after its rivals had resumed normal service.

entries.title: Russia carries out 'massive missile attack' on Ukraine
entries.description:
• Video shows Russian cruise missile flying toward Kyiv
• Ruble hits 8-month low against US dollar as sanctions bite

entries.title: Jo Mersa Marley, Reggae artist and grandson of Bob Marley, dead at 31
entries.description: Joseph, "Jo Mersa" Marley, a Reggae artist who followed in the footsteps of father, musician Stephen Marley, and grandfather, the late Reggae star Bob Marley, has died, Miami police told CNN.

entries.title: Homes on Lake Erie encased in ice after blizzard whips frigid waves onshore
entries.description: • See what massive storm did to Wisconsin store

entries.title: A Stan Lee documentary is coming to Disney+ in 2023
entries.description: The late Marvel Comics visionary Stan Lee will be the focus of an upcoming documentary.

entries.title: Kavi Sharma is American Girl's first South Asian 'Girl of the Year'
entries.description: American Girl's latest "Girl of the Year" is a spunky Broadway-loving dancer and singer -- and also the line's first-ever South Asian main character.

entries.title: Former Minneapolis police officer charged with assaulting a man during 2020 protests after death of George Floyd
entries.description: A former Minneapolis police officer is charged with assaulting a man during nighttime civil unrest following the death of George Floyd in May 2020, according to a complaint filed Wednesday.

entries.title: White House tells GOP chairmen they'll have to restart oversight requests when new Congress begins
entries.description: A top White House lawyer told two leading Republicans the oversight requests they issued during the last Congress would have to be reissued once the GOP assumes their House majority next week.

entries.title: Tourists flock to store after incredible image shows it buried under ice
entries.description: A gift shop located in Door County, Wisconsin was completely covered in ice following a winter storm. CNN affiliate WLUK has the story.

entries.title: 'White Noise' makes Adam Driver and Greta Gerwig pretty easy to tune out
entries.description: Adam Driver and writer-director Noah Baumbach follow their collaboration on the dour "Marriage Story" with a considerably quirkier Netflix movie in "White Noise," a faithful adaptation of Don DeLillo's 1985 novel that loses a great deal in translation. Baumbach's pandemic-inspired undertones resonate on that level, but it's played in such stilted fashion as to make "White Noise" pretty easy to tune out.

entries.title: Benjamin Netanyahu sworn in as leader of Israel's likely most right-wing government ever
entries.description: Benjamin Netanyahu Thursday completed a dramatic return as Israel's prime minister, after being sworn in as the leader of what is likely to be the country's most right-wing government in history.

entries.title: Here's what could tip the global economy into recession in 2023
entries.description: The global economy has endured a tough year, with decades-high inflation sapping post-lockdown spending and pushing central banks to hike borrowing costs at an unprecedented clip to bring it under control.

entries.title: Ex-Trump Cabinet secretary explains why she refuses to respond to him calling her a racist name
entries.description: Elaine Chao, who worked as the Transportation Secretary in the Trump administration, says she will not respond to former President Donald Trump calling her a racist name.

entries.title: Djokovic can't forget being deported but ready to move on in Australia
entries.description: Novak Djokovic will never forget how it felt to be deported from Australia earlier this year but the Serb said his willingness to return for next month's Grand Slam at Melbourne Park shows the depth of feeling he has for the country.

entries.title: The most unforgettable pop culture moments of 2022
entries.description: We're at the end of 2022, folks, and what a year it's been.

entries.title: Gas prices had a wild ride this year, making 2023 tough to predict
entries.description: US drivers have never seen a year quite like 2022.

entries.title: Former Pope Benedict's condition 'serious' but stable, Vatican says
entries.description: Pope Emeritus Benedict XVI's condition is "serious" but stable, the Vatican said Thursday in an update on the former pontiff's health.

entries.title: UN halts some aid programs in Afghanistan after Taliban's ban on female NGO workers
entries.description: The United Nations announced Wednesday it has suspended some of its "time-critical" programs in Afghanistan in the wake of the Taliban's ban on female NGO workers.

entries.title: Ruble hits 8-month low against dollar, as falling oil prices and sanctions bite
entries.description: Russia's currency hit an eight-month low Thursday, adding to sharp declines in December as global oil prices fell, and Western sanctions targeted Russia's energy sector.

entries.title: Eliesse Ben Seghir, 17, scores stunning brace on league debut for Monaco
entries.description: There are league debuts, and then there are league debuts à la Eliesse Ben Seghir.

entries.title: Virgin Islands attorney general sues JPMorgan Chase over banking services for Jeffrey Epstein
entries.description: The U.S. Virgin Islands government filed a lawsuit Tuesday against JPMorgan Chase, alleging that the Wall Street bank benefited financially from Jeffrey Epstein's sex trafficking operation and failed in its duty to report suspicious financial activity.

entries.title: Sesame will join the major food allergens list on January 1, FDA says
entries.description: Starting January 1, sesame will join the list of major food allergens defined by law, according to the US Food and Drug Administration.

entries.title: Erling Haaland is on course to shatter Premier League scoring record after netting 20th goal in just 15 matches
entries.description: It would seem that not even going six weeks without playing competitive football can knock Erling Haaland out of his stride.

entries.title: Three players ejected after bench-clearing brawl during Detroit Pistons and Orlando Magic game
entries.description: Three players were ejected after a clash between the Orlando Magic's Moe Wagner and Detroit Pistons guard Killian Hayes sparked a bench-clearing brawl on Wednesday.

entries.title: Meet the little-known lawyer behind Democrats' years-long battle with Trump
entries.description: House Democrats' historic decision to release former President Donald Trump's tax returns this week is the culmination of a nearly four-year legal battle orchestrated by a little-known government lawyer who rewrote the playbook for congressional investigations.

entries.title: Kylian Mbappé rescues PSG with last-gasp winner in first match since World Cup final
entries.description: Just 10 days after suffering disappointment in the World Cup final, Kylian Mbappé rescued Paris Saint-Germain with a last-gasp penalty as his side beat RC Strasbourg 2-1 in Ligue on Wednesday.

entries.title: Southwest cancellations continue as airline deals with 'meltdown' fallout
entries.description: As Southwest Airlines scrambled to get its planes back in the air and its passengers back home heading into Thursday, US Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg has taken a sharp line with the company.

entries.title: Chinese travelers are ready to go overseas again. Some countries are hesitant
entries.description: A surging Covid outbreak in China. Countries imposing travel restrictions on Chinese travelers, wary of the virus being imported. Scientists warning against fearmongering and xenophobia.

entries.title: Winter storm death toll rises to 37 in Buffalo, New York
More than 16 million under flood watches as waves of heavy snow and rain inundate Western and Central US
entries.description: As strong bouts of heavy mountain snow, widespread rain and gusty winds continue to sweep across the West and push into the Central US Thursday, more than 16 million people along the coast are under flood watches in anticipation of even more stormy weather to come.

entries.title: The new buildings set to shape the world in 2023
entries.description: The last year in architecture will be remembered as one of firsts, from the world's first "upcycled" skyscraper winning World Building of the Year to Burkina Faso-born Francis Kéré becoming the first African architect to win the coveted Pritzker Prize.

entries.title: Russian foreign minister dismissed idea of reparations for Kyiv, as well as Zelensky's idea of driving Russian troops out of occupied regions with West's help
Russia won't negotiate under terms of Zelensky's peace plan, Lavrov says
One of the world's most congested cities just opened its first metro line
entries.description: Bangladesh on Wednesday launched its first metro rail service in the capital Dhaka, with officials and commuters hopeful it will help ease traffic in one of the world's most densely populated and congested cities.

entries.title: Southwest cancellations continue as airline deals with 'meltdown' fallout
Pakistan court frees convicted rapist after 'agreement' to marry his victim
entries.description: A court in Pakistan on Monday freed a convicted rapist after it was "agreed" he would marry his victim, his lawyer said, enraging rights activists who say the ruling risks normalizing sexual violence in the South Asian country.

entries.title: Girl, 5, saves younger brother's life after car crash kills parents
entries.description: A 5-year-old girl saved her baby brother's life after a car crash killed their parents, leaving three young children trapped in the wreckage for more than two days in a remote part of rural Western Australia, CNN affiliate Nine News reported.

entries.title: Thousands of Twitter users struggle to login but Elon Musk says it 'works for me'
entries.description: Users around the world struggled to access Twitter on Wednesday—even as an error message urged "don't fret... Let's try again."

entries.title: Casino fire kills at least 2 in Cambodia border town
entries.description: At least two people were killed in a fire Wednesday that engulfed a casino hotel in a Cambodia border town popular with gamblers from neighboring Thailand, rescue officials said.

entries.title: More than 200 cars involved in massive pileup in China's Zhengzhou
entries.description: One person was killed during a massive pileup involving more than 200 vehicles in the central Chinese city Zhengzhou on Wednesday, according to state media.

entries.title: Mysterious circumstances surround deaths of these Russian tycoons
entries.description: CNN's Melissa Bell looks at the deaths of multiple members of the "Russian elite" since the war in Ukraine began.

entries.title: Winter storm death toll rises to 37 in Buffalo as criticism arises over handling of storm and cleanup
entries.description: The winter storm death toll has risen to 37 in Erie County, New York, as crews continue to clear roads and first responders check on people they couldn't reach days ago when the catastrophic weather system swept the nation, officials there said Wednesday.

entries.title: 18 children dead in Uzbekistan after consuming India-made syrup, ministry says
entries.description: At least 18 children have died in Uzbekistan after consuming a medicinal syrup manufactured by Indian drugmaker Marion Biotech, according to the Uzbek Health Ministry.

entries.title: Democratic Rep. Jamie Raskin announces he has 'serious but curable form of cancer'
entries.description: Democratic Rep. Jamie Raskin of Maryland announced on Wednesday that he has a "serious but curable form of cancer" and will begin outpatient treatment.

entries.title: Theophilus London reported missing in Los Angeles
entries.description: Theophilus London, a rapper from Trinidad and Tobago with three studio albums to his name, has been reported missing in Los Angeles, the LAPD confirmed to CNN.

entries.title: Federal prosecutors are investigating Rep.-elect George Santos' finances
entries.description: Federal prosecutors in New York are investigating the finances of Rep.-elect George Santos, a source familiar with the matter told CNN.

entries.title: Rescue drone finds missing dog stranded above frozen waterfall
entries.description: A search and rescue team in Utah reunited a family with its dog, after it spent the night in an icy canyon.

entries.title: Princeton University student who had been missing died by suicide, county prosecutor says
entries.description: The Princeton University student who was initially considered missing and was later found dead on the university's campus, died by suicide, the Mercer County Prosecutor's Office said in a news release Wednesday.
